    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What N-grams Are"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ],
            "text": "An n-gram is a contiguous sequence of n tokens"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " extracted from text by sliding a window of width n one position at a time. The parameter n determines the scope: a unigram (n=1) is a single word, a bigram (n=2) is a two-word pair, and a trigram (n=3) is a three-word group."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "N-grams bridge Bag-of-Words and full sequence models. BoW loses all word order; n-grams recover "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "italic"
              }
            ],
            "text": "local"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " order within each window while keeping the overall model simple and fast. Bigrams can distinguish \"not good\" from \"good\" and trigrams can capture phrases like \"New York City\" — things a unigram model cannot express."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Sliding window diagram showing unigrams, bigrams, and trigrams extracted from 'the cat sat on the mat'"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Token Count Formula"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For a sequence of T tokens, the number of n-grams is:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockMath",
        "attrs": {
          "latex": "\\text{count} = T - n + 1"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A 6-token sentence yields 6 unigrams, 5 bigrams, 4 trigrams, and so on. Vocabulary size grows roughly as "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "V^n"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " in the worst case, so practical systems cap n at 2 or 3 and use frequency thresholds to prune rare n-grams."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Using N-grams with scikit-learn"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Both "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "CountVectorizer"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "TfidfVectorizer"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " accept an "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "ngram_range"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " parameter. Setting it to "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "(1, 2)"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " includes both unigrams and bigrams in the same feature vector."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer\n\ncorpus = [\n    \"the cat sat on the mat\",\n    \"the dog sat on the log\",\n    \"the cat chased the dog\",\n]\n\n# Unigrams + bigrams, drop rare terms\nvec = TfidfVectorizer(\n    ngram_range=(1, 2),\n    min_df=2,          # must appear in at least 2 docs\n    max_features=20,   # cap vocabulary size\n)\nX = vec.fit_transform(corpus)\nprint(vec.get_feature_names_out())\n# ['cat', 'cat chased', 'cat sat', 'chased', 'chased the',\n#  'dog', 'dog sat', 'log', 'mat', 'on', 'on the', 'sat',\n#  'sat on', 'the', 'the cat', 'the dog', 'the log', 'the mat']\nprint(X.shape)  # (3, 18) — 18 features from 20 cap after min_df filter"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Note that "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "min_df=2"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " silently drops bigrams seen in only one document, which controls sparsity without you needing to enumerate them manually."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
